The paper discusses recent developments in deep learning-based approaches for face aging, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper specifically focuses on deep generative models, which are a type of machine learning algorithm (cs.LG). The use of deep learning also suggests that the paper may fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of aging databases, which could fall under the category of multimedia (cs.MM) or human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
